2. Difference: HashMap vs ConcurrentHashMap
    Answer:
    | Feature | HashMap | ConcurrentHashMap |
    |––––|––––|——————|
    | Thread-safe | ❌ | ✅ |
    | Locking | None | Segment-level locking |
    | Performance | Fast (single thread) | Better in concurrency |
    | Null keys | 1 key allowed | ❌ not allowed |

